Date: 7 Sep 2013
Source: Panorama.com [trans.by Mod.MPP, edited]
http://www.panorama.com.ve/portal/app/push/noticia80888.php


Five members of the Yucpa ethnic group die in suspected mass poisoning event in Perija
-----------------------
Five members of the indigenous community Yucpa from the Kasmera sector of the Yaza River in the Sierra de Perija died yesterday afternoon from an alleged poisoning after drinking liquor and eating food.

Unofficially it was learned that the community chief, came down to the Machiques hospital with the adults who had symptoms of poisoning where they died within 2 hours of being admitted to the hospital. Another 15 members of the indigenous community, including several children, had symptoms of poisoning and were taken the Our Lady of Carmen hospital in Machiques, according to Felix Garcia, director of agriculture for the Mayor of Machiques. He added that the victims were taken to the University Hospital in Maracaibo last night.

The mayor of Perija Machiques, Vidal Atencio, confirmed that 5 indigenous people were killed and announced that he would order an investigation to determine the exact causes of the deaths.

The Chiraji chief, Carlos Romero, explained in the University hospital Emergency department that the group of yucpas had been meeting and were drinking liquor since last Friday morning and then one by one they presented with the symptoms. "It began with their feeling a little bad, then they had to be taken on motorbikes, put they were not able to save them. "We want this to be investigated" stated a friend of one of the victims.

