[There are no descriptions of the illness, or the clinical signs in these people. It is possible it was methanol poisoning in the alcohol. However, without signs and symptoms and more definitive information it is not possible to speculate too far. More information from knowledgeable sources in the region would be greatly appreciated.

Venezuela may be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at: http://healthmap.org/r/4cw_. - Mod.TG]

[The Yukpa people are an Amerindian ethnic group living in the mountainous area in the border region between Colombia and Venezuela. The ethnic group has a population of approximately 10 000. The Sierra de Perija is the name of the mountain range where they live and is an extension of the eastern Andes in northern South America lying between Colombia and Venezuela. is a mountain range, an extension of the eastern Andean branch (Cordillera Oriental), in northern South America, between Colombia and Venezuela, ending further north in the Guajira Desert, a total distance of about 310 km. It separates the Maracaibo Basin (Venezuela) from the Cesar River valley (Colombia). For a map of the region, and more information, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serran%C3%ADa_del_Perij%C3%A1. For more information on the Yukpa people, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yukpa_people. - Mod.MPP]
